Georgia Gulf Corp said it filed with theSecurities and Exchange Commission for a secondary offering of4.8 mln shares of common stock, which will be sold by GeneralElectric Co's &lt;GE> General Electric Credit Corp unit andGeorgia-Pacific Corp &lt;GP>.    The company said four mln of the shares will be sold in theUnited States and 800,000 shares will be offered abroad.    Goldman, Sachs and Co is the sole manager of theunderwriting syndicate for the offering, it added. Reuter&#3;